creator: Henry Wadsworth Longfellow
description:
LibriVox recording of The Wreck of the Hesperus by Henry Wadsworth Longfellow.

Read in English by Beth Thomas; Claudia Salto; Ian King; Jason Mills; Julia Niedermaier; Leonard Wilson; MaryAnn; Nic Sebastian; Rosslyn Carlyle; and Ruth Golding.

LibriVox volunteers bring you ten recordings of "The Wreck of the Hesperus” by Henry Wadsworth Longfellow,the Fortnightly Poem for August 31, 2014. May we each be spared from the wreck of pride on the reef of Norman's Woe. (Summary by MaryAnn).

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

Download M4B (21MB)
